<br>
So i did a little looking around in luclin, talked with some mages on my server, and headed out to scarlet desert.  Here is a step by step guide <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
(Please note, this guide assumes you are not KoS to the aliens)<br>
<br>
Zone in, head right and follow the right wall out a little ways until you come to a large plateau.  Put up levitate the first time in case you get multiple pulls then you can just run off the plateau and come back, plus it's handy for running straight up the wall onto the plateau hehe.<br>
<br>
Once you are on the plateau you will see some ruins.  These ruins have the sun revenents/etc near them, there are quite a few, more than enough to keep you full of pulls at all times.  Also, up on top you will see some artifacts with aliens around them.<br>
<br>
Go sit over by the aliens and make an earth pet.  51, or 49, whichever one you prefer.  I used 51.  Don't bother burning out your pet unless you have velious legs, then do it if you want.  I'm gimp, so i don't have them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Damage shield him with your best damage shield and park him there.  Pull from maximum range with malise or malisement so your pets root sticks good.  You *should* be able to get singles every time at 55 but if two come, just split them by running off the plateau and coming back.  Works like a charm but might take a few tries to get down pat.<br>
<br>
Pull it into your pet.  Walk back a ways, to the edge of the plateau is what i usually do (more on this in a minute).  Sit and med and keep an eye on pet's health (the no-range on pet commands 'cept attack is a great boon to us).  When he is at about 17-25% and try and time your casting with your old pet landing root.  This gives you time to damage shield him before sending him in, giving you a little bit more efficiency.  If the rev is below half usually your second pet will kill him, so just hit it with a low level dd.  Sometimes they take three pets.  <br>
<br>
Nameds may spawn up here as well, and they are very easy, not much harder than the normals, maybe one more pet (3 or 4, usually 3 for me if i start out with a pet at full health).<br>
<br>
This works great and is boring, but decent and VERY safe experience.  You could go afk for a day here at the aliens and nothing would ever attack you.  Also i'm usually the only one in the zone.  Only thing to be careful of is the caster revenents (I easily resist them just put up some resist gear and elemental armor).  Only thing is, sometimes, they gate.  So just keep char memmed and if you see them gate, kindly kill them (one char was always enough for me to take them out once they were gating..usually they would be out of mana though, so they only gate about one third of the time).<br>
<br>
Anyway, hope this helps, sorry if there are any errors in here this is my first time really hunting in luclin!<br>
